Options available:
-a <1>  :  Single End Sequencing (Default)
-a <2,insertsize>  :  Paired End Sequencing. -a 2,500 implies that user has chosen Paired End Sequencing with a insert size of 500.

-p <1>  :  Illumina Platform (Default)
-p <2>  :  SOlid Platform
-p <3>  :  Pac Bio Platform

-r <specify readlength> : Deafult (40)  *For platform Illumina(1)/SOlid(2)
-r <specify mean,stdev> : This is only for Pacbio. PacBio reads follow a log normal distribution. Specify the mean and std deviation 
                          Default: 1.95,0.3

-i <specify input file path> : Defualt genome LamdaPhage

-x <specify output file 1 path for single end sequencing> : Default (current directory)
-y <specify output file 1 path for paired end sequencing> : Default (current directory)
-z <specify output file 2 path for paired end sequencing> : Default (current directory)

-g <l>  : Genome Type 1 Linear (Default)
-g <c>  : Genome Type 2 Circular 

-s : s stands for stats. You can either specify the coverage or the read numbers required. 
-s c30 would mean a coverage of 30 
-s n40 would mean No. of reads generated = 40. 
By default c10 will be taken.   

-v :verbose mode 
Type -v True to switch on the verbose mode (Default)
Type -v False to run program silently

